# CODEOWNERS — automatic reviewer assignment.
#
# Every PR that touches a path matched below requires approval from the listed
# owner(s) before it can be merged into a protected branch. Combined with
# branch protection's "Require review from Code Owners" setting, this enforces
# maintainer sign-off on detection content, pipeline code, and CI workflows.
#
# Syntax reference:
#   https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-customization/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# Patterns are matched in declaration order; the LAST matching pattern wins.
# Edit the team handles below to match your organisation. Until your real
# teams exist, the default routes everything to the repo owner.

# --- Default ----------------------------------------------------------------
*                                          @KustoKing

# --- Detection content (per-asset routing) ----------------------------------
# The six supported asset kinds (contentops/core/asset.py). Historical kinds
# live in git history and are deliberately not routed here.
detections/sentinel_analytic/**            @KustoKing
detections/sentinel_hunting/**             @KustoKing
detections/sentinel_watchlist/**           @KustoKing
detections/sentinel_parser/**              @KustoKing
detections/sentinel_data_connector/**      @KustoKing
detections/defender_custom_detection/**    @KustoKing

# --- Pipeline + workflows (platform) ----------------------------------------
contentops/**                              @KustoKing
scripts/**                                 @KustoKing
.github/**                                 @KustoKing
config/**                                  @KustoKing
docs/**                                    @KustoKing
tests/**                                   @KustoKing
SECURITY.md                                @KustoKing
